1.) No issues were present in the completion and submission of this project. 
    However, process table printout times do not quite simulate real time.

2.) To run the project, type "./oss" followed by any combination of these arguments (all of which are optional):
    a.) -h
    b.) -n [integer between 1 and 10]
    c.) -n [integer between 1 and 10, but less than or equal to integer for -n]
    d.) -t [integer of at least 1]
    e.) -i [integer between 1 and 1000]
    f.) -f [string for a logfile basename]

    Example: ./oss -n 6 -s 4 -t 3 -i 500 -f file.txt

3.) git information can be found in the '.git' folder inside this project submission. 
